        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 8:52AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 852 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ripley, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Burlison, Edith, Brownsville, Christmasville, Bonicord, Nutbush,
O'Donnell Bend, Tomato, Covington, Luckett, Forked Deer, Maury
Junction, Halls, Poplar Grove, Crockett Mills, Curve, Dog Hill,
Orysa, Brims Corner, and Tibbs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
